You can exclude some fields from being audited by using the [@NotAudited][1] annotation like this ...

```
@Audited
@Entity
class User {
  ...
  @NotAudited
  private String phoneNumber;
}
```

**EDIT:** You can control the schema of the audit table and decide exactly what info to log for each revision by creating a custom revision entity like [this][2]

In essence you define a `CustomRevisionEntity` and `CustomRevisionLister`


  [1]: https://docs.jboss.org/hibernate/orm/5.0/javadocs/org/hibernate/envers/NotAudited.html
  [2]: https://dzone.com/articles/hibernate-envers-with-custom-revision-entity

