# Use Kotlin Coroutines to Handle Threading
The reason the code is crashing is because the `Bitmap` is attempting to be created on the `Main Thread` which is not allowed since it may cause **Android Not Responding (ANR)** errors.

###Concepts Used

- **Kotlin Coroutines** [notes](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1xANxIeduaDMR2ZTZ9efkHf7YXyLs4osGnXp9odNgQNE/edit?rm=minimal).
- The **Loading, Content, Error (LCE)** pattern is used below. If interested you can learn more about it in [this talk and video](https://hackernoon.com/android-unidirectional-flow-with-livedata-bf24119e747).
- **LiveData** is used to return the data. I&#39;ve compiled my favorite **LiveData** resource in [these notes](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1e3Y126VbuZRX1-C4iKSQlFy3sfnBPkwLriDGXV9EKEU/edit?rm=minimal).
- In the *bonus code*, `toBitmap()` is a [Kotlin extension function](https://kotlinlang.org/docs/tutorials/android-plugin.html) requiring that library to be added to the app dependencies.

#Implementation

## Code
###1. Create `Bitmap` in a different thread then the `Main Thread`.
In this sample using **Kotlin Coroutines** the function is being executed in the `Dispatchers.IO` thread which is meant for CPU based operations. The function is prefixed with `suspend` which is a **Coroutine** syntax.

*Bonus* - After the `Bitmap` is created it is also compressed into an `ByteArray` so it can be passed via an `Intent` later outlined in this [full sample](https://stackoverflow.com/a/56729905/2253682).

*Repository.kt*

    suspend fun bitmapToByteArray(url: String) = withContext(Dispatchers.IO) {
        MutableLiveData&lt;Lce&lt;ContentResult.ContentBitmap&gt;&gt;().apply {
            postValue(Lce.Loading())
            postValue(Lce.Content(ContentResult.ContentBitmap(
                ByteArrayOutputStream().apply {
                    try {                     
                        BitmapFactory.decodeStream(URL(url).openConnection().apply {
                            doInput = true
                            connect()
                        }.getInputStream())
                    } catch (e: IOException) {
                       postValue(Lce.Error(ContentResult.ContentBitmap(ByteArray(0), &quot;bitmapToByteArray error or null - ${e.localizedMessage}&quot;)))
                       null
                    }?.compress(CompressFormat.JPEG, BITMAP_COMPRESSION_QUALITY, this)
               }.toByteArray(), &quot;&quot;)))
            }
        }

*ViewModel.kt*

