Edit: Here&#39;s a simple implementation utilizing `isInterrupted()` and `interrupt()`. The main-thread waits 5 seconds before interrupting the worker-thread. In this case worker-thread is basically busy-waiting, so it&#39;s not that good (looping all the time and checking `stdin.ready()`, you could of course let the worker-thread sleep for a while if no input is ready):

